#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.8/index.rst:11
msgid "Networking"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.8/index.rst:13
msgid ""
"**Revamped Traffic Management Model**. We’re finally ready to take the "
"wraps off our `new traffic management APIs "
"</blog/2018/v1alpha3-routing/>`_. We believe this new model is easier to "
"understand while covering more real world deployment `use-cases "
"</docs/tasks/traffic-management/>`_. For folks upgrading from earlier "
"releases there is a `migration guide </docs/setup/upgrade/>`_ and a "
"conversion tool built into ``istioctl`` to help convert your "
"configuration from the old model."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.8/index.rst:22
msgid ""
"**Streaming Envoy configuration**. By default Pilot now streams "
"configuration to Envoy using its `ADS API <https://github.com/envoyproxy"
"/data-plane-api/blob/master/xds_protocol.rst>`_. This new approach "
"increases effective scalability, reduces rollout delay and should "
"eliminate spurious 404 errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.8/index.rst:28
msgid ""
"**Gateway for Ingress/Egress**. We no longer support combining Kubernetes"
" Ingress specs with Istio routing rules as it has led to several bugs and"
" reliability issues. Istio now supports a platform independent `Gateway "
"</docs/concepts/traffic-management/#gateways>`_ model for ingress & "
"egress proxies that works across Kubernetes and Cloud Foundry and works "
"seamlessly with routing. The Gateway supports `Server Name Indication "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Server_Name_Indication>`_ based routing, "
"as well as serving a certificate based on the server name presented by "
"the client."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.8/index.rst:39
msgid ""
"**Constrained Inbound Ports**. We now restrict the inbound ports in a pod"
" to the ones declared by the apps running inside that pod."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.8/index.rst:43
msgid "Security"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.8/index.rst:45
msgid ""
"**Introducing Citadel**. We’ve finally given a name to our security "
"component. What was formerly known as Istio-Auth or Istio-CA is now "
"called Citadel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.8/index.rst:49
msgid ""
"**Multicluster Support**. We support per-cluster Citadel in multicluster "
"deployments such that all Citadels share the same root certificate and "
"workloads can authenticate each other across the mesh."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.8/index.rst:54
msgid ""
"**Authentication Policy**. We’ve created a unified API for "
"`authentication policy </docs/tasks/security/authentication/authn-"
"policy/>`_ that controls whether service-to-service communication uses "
"mutual TLS as well as end user authentication. This is now the "
"recommended way to control these behaviors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.8/index.rst:62
msgid "Telemetry"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.8/index.rst:64
msgid ""
"**Self-Reporting**. Mixer and Pilot now produce telemetry that flows "
"through the normal Istio telemetry pipeline, just like services in the "
"mesh."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.8/index.rst:69
msgid "Setup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.8/index.rst:71
msgid ""
"**A la Carte Istio**. Istio has a rich set of features, however you don’t"
" need to install or consume them all together. By using Helm or "
"``istioctl gen-deploy``, users can install only the features they want. "
"For example, users can install Pilot only and enjoy traffic management "
"functionality without dealing with Mixer or Citadel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.8/index.rst:78
msgid "Mixer adapters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.8/index.rst:80
msgid ""
"**CloudWatch**. Mixer can now report metrics to AWS CloudWatch. `Learn "
"more </docs/reference/config/policy-and-telemetry/adapters/cloudwatch/>`_"
msgstr ""

